postcontent: German G-43 Semi-Auto Sniper Rifle. Curio/Relic. Cal. 8x57mm Mauser. Manuf. Germany, 1944. This is one of Hitler's "Garands". They are gas operated, semi-automatic, short rifles. The first issues in early 1944 show it being used by Luftwaffe paratroopers and elite Waffen-SS divisions. In short order, other troop units wanted this rifle, but it was not until the final months of the war, that second and third echelon troops received any G43's. Most of these guns got very little use. This gun is in excellent condition. Has the normal handling dings in the stock, none serious. No cracks. Metal is clean. No rust. Matching numbers. Bore very good. Magazine original...not after-market! Original German ZF4 Sniper Scope mounted. Scope is complete with sun-shield, Rubber eye guard and original lens covers. I suspect mount is after market. title: For Sale:  18 Chinese "flatback" ak47 mags, the BEST Ak47 mags made
postcontent: I have 18 Chinese AK47 flatback magazines for sale.  If you are not familiar with this type of mag, they are made of steel like regular european mags.  What makes them differ, however, is that they lack the steel "rib" that goes up the center of the back of each mag.  This makes them much more comfortable to handle/ insert into the rifle/ and remove from the rifle.  It also makes them much easier to insert and remove from mag pouches.  The Chinese AK mags are very well known to be some of the smoothest and best feeding AK mags out there, especially when compared to Romanian and comparable mags.  15 of them are in unissued condition (mild scuffs from storage), and 3 have minor cosmetic flaws.  There are 2 that have slight dings on one side, but will still function 100% reliably.  (the third pic shows the worse of the 2 "dinged" ones)  There is also one with a small amount of storage rust. title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson Model 56, US Air Force, rare
postcontent: Here is the Holly Grail of S&W handguns, S&W model 56, serial number K502387, original finish with an excellent bore, back strap marked US. There were only 15,205 of these handguns produced serialed between K500001 to K515205, issued 1962 to 1963. Caliber .38 Special S&W, K frame revolver with adjustable target sights and two inch heavy barrel. These were replacement for Aircreman revolver, smooth back strap US marked only, Most of these were recalled and destroyed by Government and the story is that very few of these survived which makes the remaining very rare. These guns had standard S&W frame and barrel markings. This gun according to Smith and Wessen letter accompanying the gun was delivered to US Robbins Air Force Base in Warner Robbins, Georgia FFL including Arizona residents, MO or Cashier's check and 45.00 for shipping, all transactions must be concluded on internet with license holders only.

The MK1 series, developed by Primary Weapons Systems, is a significant product improvement for the M4/M16-type carbines and rifles. Utilizing our proven long stroke piston system, the MK1 series greatly reduces fouling in the action of the weapon making it as reliable as the AK47 that it was designed after. 

The MK1 series has been used in Iraq and Afghanistan, and has gained wide popularity with security personnel, law enforcement and civilians alike. 

The origins of the MK1 series began with the fascination in the simplicity and reliability of the AK47 combined with a deep-rooted appreciation for the ergonomics of the M4/M16 platform. Having a significant understanding of the deficiencies in the direct gas impingement operating system found on conventional M4/M16-style weapons, PWS developed the MK1 series with the professional in mind. 

Significant improvements have been made over both the direct gas impingement operating system and previous offerings of piston-driven operating systems. The product improvements made by PWS have addressed reliability and performance issues as well as reduced carrier tilt, cam pin wear and carrier bounce. In addition, we have one of the lightest systems on the market today! 

An innovative hand guard system utilizes a proprietary non-free float system that allows the end user or unit armorer to replace individual rails as needed without removing the barrel, barrel nut or even other rails. This system allows the user to attach numerous Picatinny rail-mounted devices such as sights, lights, and laser aiming devices. 

The PWS proprietary operating system utilizes an operating rod that is attached to the carrier and a floating head piston that is attached to the operating rod. The MK1 series is built to be a true combat carbine. With no unnecessary gas adjustments and only one moving assembly, this is the most rugged, simple and versatile piston operating system available.
